# 3d-shaders / Shadertoy GLSL

Author a single-file GLSL ES fragment shader using the Shadertoy uniform
convention (`iResolution`, `iTime`, `iFrame`, `iMouse`, ...) and render one
deterministic frame to a PNG. The headless path on macOS is the Python
`wgpu-shadertoy` library, which renders offscreen via wgpu's Metal backend — no
display needed. Pin `iTime`/`iFrame` and avoid `iDate`/`iMouse` to keep renders
byte-reproducible.

controls do
  shadertoy.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  shadertoy.source: { label: "Shader (GLSL ES)", type: "textarea", file: "src/shader.glsl" }
  shadertoy.width: { label: "Width", type: "range", min: 64, max: 1920, default: 640 }
  shadertoy.height: { label: "Height", type: "range", min: 64, max: 1080, default: 360 }
  shadertoy.time: { label: "iTime (pinned)", type: "text", default: "1.0" }
  shadertoy.frame: { label: "iFrame (pinned)", type: "text", default: "60" }
end

## Required reading

- Shadertoy Shader Development (community Claude skill) — https://mcpmarket.com/zh/tools/skills/shadertoy-shader-development
- Shader Development Toolkit: GLSL & VFX (community) — https://mcpmarket.com/tools/skills/shader-development-toolkit
- GLSL Shader Development (community) — https://mcpmarket.com/tools/skills/glsl-shader-development
- wgpu-shadertoy (BSD-2-Clause) — https://github.com/pygfx/shadertoy
- No official Anthropic shader skill — https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/agents-and-tools/agent-skills

## Render

```bash
# install (one time)
python3 -m venv /tmp/stv && /tmp/stv/bin/pip install wgpu-shadertoy pillow numpy

# render one deterministic frame to PNG
/tmp/stv/bin/python -c "from wgpu_shadertoy import Shadertoy; import numpy as np; from PIL import Image; code=open('src/shader.glsl').read(); s=Shadertoy(code, resolution=(640,360), offscreen=True); f=s.snapshot(time_float=1.0, frame=60); Image.fromarray(np.asarray(f)).save('out.png'); print('ok')"

# video kind (secondary): sweep frames -> ffmpeg, or use shady/glsl-to-mp4
```

## Failure modes

- Using `iDate` or `iMouse` breaks single-frame determinism — exclude them.
- `mainImage` signature must be `void mainImage(out vec4 fragColor, in vec2 fragCoord)`.
- Multi-buffer shaders (Buffer A-D) need FBO support — plain wgpu-shadertoy single-pass won't render them; use `shady` or scrygl.
- OpenGL-based tools (shadertoy-render, glsl-to-mp4) may need an offscreen GL context on macOS; prefer wgpu/Metal for the image kind.
- Video kind needs ffmpeg: `brew install ffmpeg`.
